abstract: Between the Festival of Contemporary Music and Boston Symphony Orchestra programs, a recent visit offered an exhilarating immersion.
snippet: Between the Festival of Contemporary Music and Boston Symphony Orchestra programs, a recent visit offered an exhilarating immersion.
lead_paragraph: LENOX, Mass. — There are really two Tanglewoods here in the bucolic Berkshires. One is the popular summer home of the Boston Symphony Orchestra. The other is the less-known Tanglewood Music Center, the orchestra’s prestigious training institute for exceptional student performers and composers.

headline_main: Take Apart in Order to Reproduce

abstract: Julián Castro, Tulsi Gabbard, Kirsten Gillibrand and Tom Steyer are getting closer to qualifying, and they’re urgently seeking supporters who can help them earn a spot onstage.
snippet: Julián Castro, Tulsi Gabbard, Kirsten Gillibrand and Tom Steyer are getting closer to qualifying, and they’re urgently seeking supporters who can help them earn a spot onstage.
lead_paragraph: [Update: Julián Castro was the 10th and final Democratic candidate to qualify for the September debate.]

abstract: Secret rooms have appeared throughout history, in medieval castles and Prohibition-era speakeasies. Now they’re popping up in workplaces.
snippet: Secret rooms have appeared throughout history, in medieval castles and Prohibition-era speakeasies. Now they’re popping up in workplaces.
lead_paragraph: Transparency is one of the biggest trends in modern office design: open floor plans, fewer offices, glass walls and doors. And at a time when #MeToo has called attention to the sordid things that can happen behind closed doors, there may be some comfort in having everything, and everyone, within view.

headline_main: 4 Days, 20 Democrats. Who Won the Iowa State Fair?

abstract: In the On Politics newsletter: Lessons from a sweaty, calorie-filled weekend at the state fair. Plus, riding the Ferris wheel with Cory Booker.
